# Project Defaults

This is an Express.js + TypeScript backend with **Mongoose** (MongoDB), **Prisma** (PostgreSQL), and **MySQL/MariaDB**.

## Skills to Follow

Always reference these project skills when relevant:
- `.agents/skills/express-rest-api` — routing, middleware, validation, error handling
- `.agents/skills/nodejs-backend-patterns` — layered architecture, DI, auth, caching
- `.agents/skills/mongoose` — Mongoose ODM (8.x/9.x), TypeScript integration, performance best practices
- `.agents/skills/mongoose-mongodb` — MongoDB data layers with Mongoose, schema design, indexing, virtuals, middleware hooks
- `.agents/skills/mongodb` — MongoDB connection, CRUD, aggregation, indexing
- `.agents/skills/prisma-postgres` — PostgreSQL schema, migrations, queries
- `.agents/skills/mysql` — MySQL/MariaDB schema, indexing, query tuning, transactions
- `.agents/skills/sequelize` — Sequelize ORM models, associations, migrations, queries

## TypeScript Rules

- Avoid `any` — create proper types/interfaces
- Use `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions/intersections
- Use PascalCase for types, camelCase for variables/functions, kebab-case for files
- Use Zod for runtime validation with inferred types
- Prefer `const` objects over enums

## Architecture

- **Layered**: Routes → Controllers → Services → Repositories
- Business logic lives in `services/`, never in route handlers
- All errors flow through the centralized error handler middleware
- Environment config lives in `src/config/index.ts` — never hardcode secrets
- Use graceful shutdown for database connections (already in `server.ts`)
